% Write `pdd/checkup_apply.py` implementing human-approved patch application for prompt coaching suggestions.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

<responsibility>
This module validates, presents, and applies `ApplyPatch` objects to `.prompt` and
`user_stories/story__*.md` files after per-patch human approval. It owns the TTY
guard, interactive approval loop, atomic backup+write, and apply log. It does NOT
generate coaching suggestions — the caller (checkup coach) provides the patches.
</responsibility>

<non_responsibilities>
- Does not generate or score coaching suggestions.
- Does not authenticate users or check permissions.
- Does not modify `src/`, generated `pdd/` modules, or policy-review targets.
- Does not auto-apply by confidence score.
- Does not perform CI or non-interactive apply.
</non_responsibilities>

<vocabulary>
- ApplyPatch: A Pydantic model representing one proposed edit (patch_kind, target_path, draft, section_tag, patch_id).
- DeterministicError: An exception raised when a patch cannot safely be applied (section absent, path traversal, etc.).
- patch_kind: One of `vocabulary_line`, `vocabulary_section_create`, `coverage_line`, `contract_rule_line`, `waiver_entry`, `story_create`, `story_covers_append`.
- dry_run: When True, diffs are computed and displayed but no files are written and no backups are created.
- already_present: A patch status used when the canonical content already appears verbatim in the target section; treated as a no-op.
- approved patch: A patch the user accepted via the [y]es prompt choice.
- TTY context: A context where both sys.stdin.isatty() and sys.stdout.isatty() return True.
</vocabulary>

<contract_rules>
R1 - apply requires interactive
The system MUST NOT write any file when `--apply` is used without `--interactive`.
The system MUST raise `click.UsageError` with a message mentioning both flags before loading any patches.

R2 - TTY guard
The system MUST check `sys.stdin.isatty() and sys.stdout.isatty()` before presenting any patch.
When not in a TTY context, the system MUST raise `click.UsageError` before reading or displaying patches.
The system MUST NOT check TTY per-patch; the check fires once at session start.

R3 - dry-run leaves files unchanged
When `dry_run=True`, the system MUST compute and display the unified diff for each approved patch but MUST NOT write any file and MUST NOT create any backup.
The system MUST record `dry_run: true` in the apply log.

R4 - interactive approval choices
For each patch, the system MUST prompt `[y]es / [n]o / [e]dit / [s]kip remaining` with default `n`.
`y` — accept and apply the patch.
`n` — skip this patch (status: `skipped`).
`e` — open `patch.draft` in `$EDITOR` via `click.edit()`; if the user saves, replace draft with edited text, then apply.
`s` — skip this patch and all remaining patches immediately.

R5 - path safety
The system MUST resolve `target_path` relative to the repo root and MUST raise `DeterministicError` when the resolved path escapes the repo root or when the path does not end in `.prompt` or match `user_stories/story__*.md`.

R6 - section-aware insertion
For section-insert patch kinds (`vocabulary_line`, `coverage_line`, `contract_rule_line`, `waiver_entry`), the applicator MUST locate the closing `</tag>` of the target section and insert the new content immediately before it.
When the target section tag is absent, the applicator MUST raise `DeterministicError` unless `force_apply=True`.

R7 - idempotency
Before inserting content, the applicator MUST check whether the canonical content already appears verbatim in the section. If it does, the applicator MUST return the text unchanged and record `status: already_present`.

R8 - story_create uniqueness
`story_create` MUST use `open(path, 'x')` (exclusive-create mode) so it fails if the file already exists, unless `force_overwrite_story=True`.

R9 - atomic backup and write
For each approved, non-dry-run patch, the system MUST:
  1. Create parent directories for the backup path `.pdd/evidence/checkups/backups/<run_id>/<original_filename>`.
  2. Copy the original file to the backup path before writing.
  3. Write the modified content via `atomic_write_text` (temp-in-dir + fsync + os.replace).

R10 - apply log
The system MUST write `.pdd/evidence/checkups/apply-<run_id>.json` after all patches are processed.
The apply log MUST validate against schema version `pdd.checkup_apply.v1`.
The apply log MUST be written via `atomic_write_json` even on partial failure (patches applied before error retain their records).

R11 - deterministic error blocking
Patches that raise `DeterministicError` MUST be recorded with `status: error` and MUST NOT be written unless `force_apply=True`.
When `force_apply=False` and a deterministic error occurs, the system MUST display the error to the user and skip the patch.

R12 - postflight contract check
After apply (non-dry-run), the system MUST re-run `pdd checkup contract check` on every touched `.prompt` file and print suggested next steps.
When `verify_strict=True`, the postflight exit code MUST propagate to the command's exit code.

R13 - privacy
The system MUST NOT log, display, or write raw bearer tokens, API keys, or secrets appearing in patch drafts.
</contract_rules>

<capabilities>
- MAY read `.prompt` and `user_stories/story__*.md` files.
- MAY write `.prompt` and `user_stories/story__*.md` files (only after human approval).
- MAY write backup files under `.pdd/evidence/checkups/backups/<run_id>/`.
- MAY write apply log at `.pdd/evidence/checkups/apply-<run_id>.json`.
- MAY invoke `$EDITOR` via `click.edit()` for the `[e]dit` path.
- MAY invoke `pdd checkup contract check` as a subprocess for postflight.
- MUST NOT write to `src/`, generated `pdd/` modules, or policy-check targets.
- MUST NOT auto-apply without human approval.
- MUST NOT call any LLM or cloud service.
</capabilities>

<coverage>
R1: acceptance criteria "–apply without –interactive → clear error"
R2: acceptance criteria "non-TTY → error, no silent write"
R3: acceptance criteria "–dry-run leaves file bytes unchanged"
R4: TODO add story for interactive y/n/e/s loop before production use
R5: TODO add story for path traversal rejection
R6: TODO add story for section-not-found deterministic error
R7: TODO add idempotency story
R8: acceptance criteria "story_create fails if file exists"
R9: TODO add atomic backup+write story
R10: acceptance criteria "Apply log JSON validates against pdd.checkup_apply.v1"
R11: acceptance criteria "Deterministic errors block apply unless –force-apply"
R12: TODO add postflight story
R13: TODO add privacy story
</coverage>

% Requirements
1. Define `ApplyPatch` (Pydantic v2 `BaseModel`): fields `patch_id` (str, default uuid4), `patch_kind` (Literal of 7 kinds), `target_path` (str), `draft` (str), `section_tag` (Optional[str], default None), `description` (Optional[str], default None).
2. Define `PatchStatus` enum: `applied`, `skipped`, `error`, `already_present`, `dry_run_preview`.
3. Define `PatchResult` (Pydantic v2): `patch_id`, `patch_kind`, `target_path`, `status` (PatchStatus), `diff_unified` (Optional[str]), `backup_path` (Optional[str]), `error_message` (Optional[str]), `ts` (str ISO-8601).
4. Define `ApplyRunResult` (Pydantic v2): `schema_version` (Literal "pdd.checkup_apply.v1"), `run_id`, `dry_run` (bool), `patches` (List[PatchResult]), `postflight` (Optional[dict]).
5. Define `DeterministicError(Exception)`.
6. Implement six pure applicator functions — each accepts `(patch: ApplyPatch, file_text: str) -> str` and raises `DeterministicError` on invalid state:
   - `apply_vocabulary_line`: inserts `draft` before `</vocabulary>`.
   - `apply_vocabulary_section_create`: creates a `<vocabulary>\n{draft}\n</vocabulary>` block before `<contract_rules>` opening or at end of file if absent.
   - `apply_coverage_line`: inserts `draft` before `</coverage>`.
   - `apply_contract_rule_line`: inserts `draft` before `</contract_rules>`.
   - `apply_waiver_entry`: inserts `draft` before `</waivers>`.
   - `apply_story_covers_append`: appends `draft` to the `## Covers` section of a story file.
7. For `story_create`: handled in `run_checkup_apply` directly (not a pure applicator), using `open(path, 'x')`.
8. Implement `apply_patch(patch, file_text) -> str` — dispatcher calling the correct applicator by `patch_kind`; raises `DeterministicError` for unknown kinds.
9. Implement `run_checkup_apply(patches, *, run_id: Optional[str] = None, dry_run, force_apply, verify_strict, force_overwrite_story) -> ApplyRunResult`. When `run_id` is `None`, auto-generate a UUID4 string at session start (same pattern as `patch_id` in `ApplyPatch`).
   - Validate TTY upfront (R2).
   - Validate each `target_path` (R5).
   - For each patch: display unified diff via `difflib.unified_diff` with Click colour, prompt `[y/n/e/s]`, apply, backup, write atomically.
   - Write apply log (R10).
   - Run postflight contract check on touched prompts (R12).
10. Use `atomic_write_text` from `pdd.json_atomic` for all prompt/story file writes.
11. Use `atomic_write_json` from `pdd.json_atomic` for the apply log.
12. Colour diff output: red for `-` lines, green for `+` lines, via `click.style`.
13. Import `parse_prompt_contracts` from `pdd.contract_ir` for postflight (not for applicators).

